<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2580] Make the hlog file names unique</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2580</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the HLog archiving thread adds another timestamp to ensure the file names are &quot;unique&quot;. This is ugly and makes it harder to track the HLogs movements from outside (like replication). Instead we could use a UUID as the file name. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was discussing with Stack the need of keeping a timestamp in the file name... I think we can&apos;t get rid of it since we need to read the HLogs in sequence when splitting.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
