                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12869812" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 20 May 2010 23:40:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch adds the region server hostname and port (encoded) as the prefix for the log file name. All the other modifications are refactoring around that. Passes all unit tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12869817" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 21 May 2010 00:14:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Last patch was still putting a ts in front of the log file when moving it, this one doesn&apos;t.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12869818" author="stack" created="Fri, 21 May 2010 00:33:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Only blog should know how file name is formatted so move the parse of filename there.   The encoding should also be in blog.  What if u are passed a prefix string that is illegal as part of a filename in hdfs?   The javadoc on prefix needs to be beefier suggesting hostnAme and port as prefix when in distributed en ironmenr and thAt blog will be used if none supplied. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fix Above and I am +1 commit&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12869828" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 21 May 2010 01:07:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that includes Stack&apos;s comments. Will commit unless some objects.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12869845" author="stack" created="Fri, 21 May 2010 03:32:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On commit, change this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+    this.prefix = prefix == null ? &quot;hlog&quot; : URLEncoder.encode(prefix, &quot;UTF8&quot;);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Prefix could be &quot;&quot;.  Test for length too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would this ever be a valid condition:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+    if (filenum &amp;lt; 0) return null;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Throw an exception, RuntimeException if you have to.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12870106" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 21 May 2010 18:50:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk with Stack&apos;s and Ryan&apos;s comments.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017455" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:43:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
